page.title: 11ETTON-2
page.content: (CONT.FROM P.10) been taken over by a building firm which has large premises in the village and provides jobs for the erstwhile farm workers. The appearance of the village has changed.There is no longer so much movement of livestock through the village from farms to outlying fields, and there are more cars and tractors about. The Processed Pea,a folk club, run by the landlord of the village pub attracts visitors and entertainers from around Humberside and Yorkshire. The village also has a stud breeding thoroughbreds and Mountain Moorlands & the'Kennels',a large house thought to contain the remains of an old monastery,where the Holderness Hunt pack is kept.There is also a village pond with a variety of wild ducks feeding there.
